 =?UTF-8?q?=5FLFB?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Wave 2 (patches 0010+0011) successfully engaged the LFB fast path on
real Cirrus / Mach64 hardware (vram_ptr in mapped LFB confirmed). But
the page-flipping logic that comes for free on LFB modes turned out to
be the wrong choice for Cave Story's 2-15 fps target:

Symptom (real-HW Cirrus, /tmp/cirrus2/SDLDBG.LOG):
  - line 180: UpdateWindowFramebuffer #1   vram_ptr=77c25800  (page 1)
  - line 184: UpdateWindowFramebuffer #100 vram_ptr=77c00000  (page 0)
  - 0x25800 = 153600 bytes = exactly one 320x240x16bpp frame.

User-visible: the boot "Loading..." splash sticks while the engine
renders into the off-screen page; the visible page only updates on a
PageSet (`__dpmi_int 0x10, ax=0x4F07`) call that either silently fails
on the M64VBE ROM or selects a stale page on the next flip.

The post-flush block in SDL_dosframebuffer.c (around line 880) does
contain a VBE 0x4F07 call, but the rotation it performs assumes a
working PageSet that on Mach64 + M64VBE doesn't reliably swap the
displayed image. We don't need page-flipping at our target framerate —
single-buffered with potential tearing is invisible at 2-15 fps.

Two-pronged fix:

1. SDL_dosframebuffer.c populate_fb_state_for_direct_fb (Path B helper
   from patch 0011): always select page_offset[0] as the WRITE target
   regardless of `data->page_flip_available`. The WRITE always lands on
   the visible page.

2. SDL_dosmodes.c DOSVESA_SetDisplayMode: gate the
   `data->page_flip_available = true` block on
   !SDL_GetHintBoolean(SDL_HINT_DOS_PREFER_LFB, false). When the
   PREFER_LFB hint (which doskutsu sets unconditionally on DJGPP) is
   active, page_flip_available stays false. The post-flush rotation
   block at SDL_dosframebuffer.c:880 gates on
   `vdata->page_flip_available` so it becomes a no-op — no VBE 0x4F07
   calls, no vram_ptr swap. Belt-and-braces consistency with #1.

Verified under DOSBox-X parity smoke (build/stage/SDLDBG.LOG, fast cycles,
~900 flushes captured):
  mode-set #1 (exit ok): banked_mode=0 mapping.size=2097152 page_flip=0
  UpdateWindowFramebuffer #1:   ... vram_ptr=dfc00000 ...
  UpdateWindowFramebuffer #100: ... vram_ptr=dfc00000 ...
  UpdateWindowFramebuffer #200: ... vram_ptr=dfc00000 ...
  ... (stable through #900)

vram_ptr stable across all 900 sampled flushes — single page, no
rotation. Wave-2's alternation behavior is gone.

Trade-off accepted: lose double-buffer tear-prevention. At Cave Story's
2-15 fps target the visual cost is invisible. If a future higher-fps
mode (Phase 9 final gate is 15 fps; nothing above that on the roadmap
yet) wants proper double-buffering, restore VBE PageSet plumbing then.

Why DOS needs this
------------------
Real-HW Cirrus / Mach64 + M64VBE ROM treatment of VBE function 0x4F07
(Set Display Start) does not produce a stable visible image when
combined with the SDL3-DOS driver's per-flush page rotation. Found
empirically via the wave-2 capture; not a problem on DOSBox-X parity
because its emulated VBE PageSet is a memcpy. DOS-only fix in the DOS
backend.

Local-only patch per workspace policy (memory note "SDL upstream —
local patches only"): never PR'd upstream.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c | 22 ++++++++++++++++++++--
 src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c       | 16 +++++++++++++++-
 2 files changed, 35 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c
index 418189449..4594ab5da 100644
--- a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c
+++ b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c
@@ -343,8 +343,26 @@ static bool populate_fb_state_for_direct_fb(SDL_VideoDevice *device,
 
     if (use_lfb_path) {
         // LFB nearptr — DPMI-mapped VRAM linear address.
-        int back_page = data->page_flip_available ? (1 - data->current_page) : 0;
-        fb_state.vram_ptr = (Uint8 *)DOS_PhysicalToLinear(data->mapping.address) + data->page_offset[back_page];
+        //
+        // DOSKUTSU patch 0014 (Phase 9 wave 3, Fix A): force single-buffered
+        // page 0 always. The previous logic selected `1 - current_page` as
+        // the WRITE target whenever `page_flip_available` was true, but the
+        // post-flush block at line ~880 then calls VBE 0x4F07 to swap the
+        // DISPLAYED page and rotate vram_ptr. On real Cirrus / Mach64
+        // hardware that swap either silently fails or leaves the wrong page
+        // visible — symptom: the boot-time "Loading…" splash sticks while
+        // the engine renders into the invisible page (`vram_ptr` alternates
+        // between `0x77c00000` and `0x77c25800` per /tmp/cirrus2 SDLDBG.LOG
+        // line 184 vs 180). DOSVESA_SetDisplayMode also force-disables
+        // page_flip_available when DOS_PREFER_LFB is set, so this is belt-
+        // and-braces consistency: regardless of the upstream flag, the
+        // helper writes into page 0 and the post-flush block (which gates
+        // on `vdata->page_flip_available`) becomes a no-op. Trade-off
+        // accepted: lose double-buffer tear-prevention. At Cave Story's
+        // 2-15 fps target this is invisible. If a higher-fps mode wants
+        // proper double-buffering later, restore VBE PageSet plumbing
+        // then.
+        fb_state.vram_ptr = (Uint8 *)DOS_PhysicalToLinear(data->mapping.address) + data->page_offset[0];
         fb_state.vram_phys = 0;
         fb_state.use_dosmemput = false;
         fb_state.banked_multibank = false;
diff --git a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c
index 8cdbf34bc..dd4e7a6b5 100644
--- a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c
+++ b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c
@@ -848,7 +848,21 @@ bool DOSVESA_SetDisplayMode(SDL_VideoDevice *device, SDL_VideoDisplay *sdl_displ
     // we would still need to bank-switch through the same 64KB window to write
     // to the back page, so the performance benefit is minimal (just tear-free).
     // For simplicity, disable page-flipping in banked mode for now.
-    if (!data->banked_mode && modedata->num_image_pages >= 1) {
+    //
+    // DOSKUTSU patch 0014 (Phase 9 wave 3, Fix A): when SDL_HINT_DOS_PREFER_LFB
+    // is set, also force-disable page-flipping. The post-flush rotation in
+    // SDL_dosframebuffer.c (`__dpmi_int(0x10, ax=0x4F07)` plus vram_ptr swap)
+    // does not produce a stable visible image on Cirrus / Mach64 + M64VBE in
+    // wave-2 testing — symptom is the boot splash sticking while the engine
+    // renders to the off-screen page. Forcing single-buffered page 0 makes
+    // every frame land on the visible page; the post-flush block becomes a
+    // no-op because it gates on `page_flip_available`. Pairs with the
+    // `populate_fb_state_for_direct_fb` change to always select page 0 as
+    // the WRITE target. Trade-off: lose tear-prevention double-buffering;
+    // accepted for the 2-15 fps target.
+    const bool prefer_lfb_no_flip =
+        SDL_GetHintBoolean(SDL_HINT_DOS_PREFER_LFB, false);
+    if (!data->banked_mode && modedata->num_image_pages >= 1 && !prefer_lfb_no_flip) {
         data->page_flip_available = true;
         data->current_page = 0;
         data->page_offset[0] = 0;
